</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0175-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0175-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Col. John Armstrong reported that Coll Washington told me, if he came [to Fort Cumberland] without Erecting something by the way, that it was not in his power to be early enough to assist the Garrison, nor woud all his men be more than a Breakfast to the French &amp; their Indians (Armstrong to William Denny, 19 June 1757, <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Samuel Hazard et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;Pennsylvania Archives&lt;/i&gt;. 9 ser., 138 vols. Philadelphia and Harrisburg, 18521949. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Pa. Archives</span></span>, 1st ser., 3:18789).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0175-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0175-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0090" class="document">especially Stanwix to GW, 23 May</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0096" class="document">GW to Stanwix, 28 May</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0141" class="document">Edward Shippen to GW, 17 June 1757</a>.</p>

